Four people have been arrested for possession of stolen property and will appear in court soon. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - There is a heavy police presence in Jeppestown, Johannesburg after cars were damaged and shops looted. Four people have been arrested for possession of stolen property and will appear in court soon. READ: Violence flares up in Jeppestown overnight The unrest erupted after 3 people burnt to death in an abandoned building in Karl Street. Investigators are still trying to determine the cause of the fire and are talking to witnesses who survived.